Definition: an action brought to recover damages from a person whose actions have resulted indirectly in injury or loss
Example: a person struck by a log as it was thrown onto a road could maintain trespass against the thrower but one who was hurt by stumbling over it could maintain and action on the case
Synonyms: trespass, an, action, brought, to, recover, damages, from, a, person, whose, actions, have, resulted, indirectly, in, injury, or, loss, struck, by, log, as, it, was, thrown, onto, road, could, maintain, against, the, thrower, but, one, who, hurt, stumbling, over, and, on, case
Category: noun.act
